Package org.biopax.paxtools.util

This package contains various collections and utilities that is used by the other packages and modules of paxtools.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BPCollections.CollectionProvider This interface is responsible for setting the class and initialize and load factor for all sets and maps used in all model objects for performance purposes.
Filter<T> Generic interface for defining filter decorators.
 

Class Summary
AbstractFilterSet<F,E> Base class for implementing various filter sets.
AccessibleSet<E> This is a decorator set for capturing a set member that is equal to the given parameter.
BasicFilterFactory Basic filter factory implementation class.
BiopaxSafeSet<E extends BioPAXElement> A thread-safe set of BioPAX objects that also prevents adding several elements having the same URI.
ClassFilterSet<E,F extends E> A FilterSet that filters based on the class.
CompositeIterator<T> A composite iterator that iterates over multiple iterators.
DataSourceFieldBridge A FieldBridge implementation for including dataSource (Provenance) names and URIs to the BioPAX element's Lucene index.
DataSourceFilterFactory A Filter factory implementation to define the full-text search filter "by data source".
EquivalenceGrouper<T extends BioPAXElement> Utility class for equivalence based comparison of a set of BioPAXElements.
OrganismFieldBridge A FieldBridge implementation for including organism (BioSource) names, ids, terms to parent BioPAX element's index.
OrganismFilterFactory A Filter factory implementation to define the full-text search filter "by organism".
ParentPathwayFieldBridge This is a FieldBridge implementation for biopax elements to generate a custom search/filter index field that contain their parent pathway URIs and names.
SetEquivalenceChecker This class performs set operations based on equivalence.
SetStringBridge Hibernate - Lucene bridge between Set and String.
XrefFieldBridge This Hibernate search field bridge implementation is to be applied to the 'xref' object properties of many biopax XReferrable classes, such as EntityReference, Protein, etc., and allows finding these objects by some identifier (e.g., UniProt, HGNC Symbol, etc.).
 

Enum Summary
AnnotationMapKey Deprecated. this enumeration is not used and probably not required at all.
BPCollections  
 

Exception Summary
BioPaxIOException This exception is thrown if a problem occurs during an input/output operation related to BioPAX Handlers.
IllegalBioPAXArgumentException This exception is thrown typically when BioPAX domain or cardinality restrictions are violated.
IllegalRDFIDException This exception is thrown when an object does not have a proper, non-null, unique id.
 

Annotation Types Summary
AutoComplete Interface for demarcating excise-able boundaries of the object graph.
